    • Class org.semanticweb.yars.nx.NodeComparator extends java.lang.Object implements Serializable

      serialVersionUID:
      1L

      • Serialized Fields

        • _variableLength

          boolean _variableLength
          if true, returns true for equals and 0 for compareTo if both arrays contain same elements in same indices even if both arrays are of different lengths. If false arrays of different length with return false and non-zero for equals and compareTo.

        • _nZero

          boolean _nZero
          Not zero only returns zero if references are the same (allows for duplicates).

        • _nEquals

          boolean _nEquals
          Not equals ensures only comparison on reference (if same object, allows duplicates).

        • _numeric

          boolean[] _numeric
          Mask stating which elements should be ordered (compare only) numerically

        • _reverse

          boolean[] _reverse
          Mask stating which elements should be reverse ordered (compare only)

        • _order

          int[] _order
          Checks the nodes in the given order for the compare to method For example for sorting in POCS order, use order = {1, 2, 3, 0}. Also, an element which does not affect sorting order can be omitted. For example, to compare only on POC for SPOC quad, use {1, 2, 3}.

        • _n

          int _n
          Only consider at most first n nodes for equals and compare
